# CodeStep Frontend Rules

## Package Manager
- **Always use `yarn`**, never `npm` or `npx`.
  - Install deps: `yarn add <package>`
  - Run scripts: `yarn dev`, `yarn build`, `yarn lint`
  - Do NOT generate or reference `package-lock.json`

---

## JSX — No Inline Logic

Never write conditional logic or complex expressions directly inside JSX.  
Extract them into named variables **before** the return statement.

```tsx
// ❌ Bad
return (
  <div>
    {user.role === 'admin' && isLoggedIn ? <AdminPanel /> : <GuestView />}
  </div>
)

// ✅ Good
const showAdminPanel = user.role === 'admin' && isLoggedIn
const content = showAdminPanel ? <AdminPanel /> : <GuestView />

return <div>{content}</div>
```

This applies to:
- Ternary expressions with JSX on either branch
- `&&` short-circuit renders that are more than one token
- `.map()` calls longer than a single simple expression
- Any condition derived from more than one variable

---

## Component Extraction

Any JSX block that is **repeated 2 or more times**, or that is **self-contained and longer than ~10 lines**, must be extracted into its own component file.

```tsx
// ❌ Bad — duplicated inline
<span className="bg-white/5 border border-white/10 text-sm px-3 py-1 rounded-full">
  React 19
</span>
<span className="bg-white/5 border border-white/10 text-sm px-3 py-1 rounded-full">
  TypeScript
</span>

// ✅ Good — single reusable component
// src/components/ui/Badge.tsx
export function Badge({ label }: { label: string }) {
  return (
    <span className="bg-white/5 border border-white/10 text-sm px-3 py-1 rounded-full">
      {label}
    </span>
  )
}
```

---

## File & Folder Structure

```
src/
├── components/
│   ├── ui/          # Primitive, reusable atoms (Button, Badge, Card, Input…)
│   └── layout/      # Page-level shells (Header, Sidebar, PageWrapper…)
├── features/        # Domain slices — each folder owns its components + hooks
│   └── roadmap/
│       ├── RoadmapPage.tsx
│       ├── RoadmapNode.tsx
│       └── useRoadmap.ts
├── hooks/           # Shared custom hooks
├── lib/             # Pure utility functions, API client setup
├── types/           # Shared TypeScript types & interfaces
└── pages/           # Route-level entry points (thin, delegates to features/)
```

- One component per file. File name matches the exported component name (PascalCase).
- Hooks live in files prefixed with `use` (e.g. `useAuth.ts`).
- Utility functions live in `src/lib/`, not inside components.

---

## TypeScript

- **No `any`**. Use `unknown` and narrow, or define a proper type.
- Define prop types with an `interface` immediately above the component.
- Prefer explicit return types on hooks and utility functions.
- Use `type` for unions/aliases, `interface` for object shapes.

```tsx
// ✅
interface BadgeProps {
  label: string
  variant?: 'default' | 'primary'
}

export function Badge({ label, variant = 'default' }: BadgeProps) { … }
```

---

## Styling (Tailwind CSS v4)

- Use Tailwind utility classes directly; avoid inline `style={{}}` except for truly dynamic values (e.g. calculated widths).
- Group classes logically: layout → spacing → typography → color → effects.
- If a class list exceeds ~6 classes, consider extracting a semantic CSS class with `@apply` in `index.css`.
- Never use `!important` overrides.

---

## Naming Conventions

| Thing | Convention | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Component | PascalCase | `RoadmapNode.tsx` |
| Hook | camelCase prefixed `use` | `useRoadmapProgress.ts` |
| Utility fn | camelCase | `formatXP.ts` |
| Type/Interface | PascalCase | `UserProgress` |
| Constants | SCREAMING_SNAKE | `MAX_STREAK_DAYS` |
| CSS class (custom) | kebab-case | `.card-glow` |

---

## API Calls

- All backend requests go through the `/api` proxy (never hardcode `localhost:3000` in component code).
- Centralise fetch logic in `src/lib/api.ts`; components call typed helper functions, not raw `fetch`.
- Use `VITE_API_URL` from `.env` only inside `vite.config.ts` — never import it in component code.
